title: The Temperature Dependence of Neutron Inelastic Scattering from Water

x4freetext: The Temperature Dependence of Neutron Inelastic

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Knolls Atomic Power Lab. report series, No.3908 (1970)

x4codes.hlp: Knolls Atomic Power Laboratory, Schenectady, NY, United States of America

x4freetext: Pressurized water container: 13 cm wide x 20 cm high.
Resolution function, the standard deviation of
the neutron pulse along the incident flight path, at
x**2 sigma-tau **2, where C(0) is the covariance
along the path at zero and sigma-tau **2 is square of
the standard deviation of the tau distribution of
neutrons in the pulse. This relation holds for pulses
